<br>
here is something I tend to do when I CC, seems to work, but am open to new ideas if anyone has them.<br>
<br>
when I CC, and i have only one add, I like to charm the mob instead of mez.<br>
<br>
My assist key is set up as:<br>
<br>
/assist tank<br>
/pause 2<br>
/pet attack<br>
<br>
this works in a few ways.<br>
<br>
one, if I am charming, it allows me to reingage the MA mob while telling the pet to attack....I twist 3 songs, hit F1 twice, to re-target pet, count to 2, start charm song again (then hit the assist hokey while the song is going off so that I can keep swinging while the pet is getting re-charmed.) (obviously this is not 100% fullproof....since resists can come into play)<br>
<br>
I hardly ever mez a mob if only one add, but will do the same thing as above when mezing.  This allows you to keep meleeing, mez/charm, and twist with little skip of the beat.<br>
<br>
...<br>
<br>
I will aslo, in a big pull, after killing most of the adds and left with 2 mobs, will go up to one of the mezzed ones, start charm, then hit the attack button right before charm goes off....then go back to assisting the main tank....<br>
<br>
I love to see the frogie shaman in Sebilis slow their fellow frogs, love to see them cast Gflux on their own buddies or nukem dead...hehe<br>
<br>
what can I say, I am a sadistic beotch....RAAAR<br>
<br>
