Evesong <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvennyenn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>vennyenn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.theshadoworder.com/images/sigs/eye.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/14/02 12:35:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumbard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=417.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theshadoworder.com/images/sigs/joxur_icon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crowd Control [Was: Twisting]</span><hr size=1> Hmm, I never charm anymor.  I've been exp'ing in luclin zones where randomly a mob can be too high level to charm.  Also been grouping with a shaman or chanter a lot so I like to keep them mezzed so they can slow the mobs ahead of time.<br>
<br>
I'm pretty basic..  I have all 8 songs in my first 8 hotkey slots, then my mez/oos/inc message in slot 9, and assist in 10.<br>
<br>
While doing CC in exp groups, I always always use external view to target mobs.  I always face the mob the MA is attacking.   Then, I:<br>
<br>
1) Stop song<br>
2) Target the add mob<br>
3) begin singing mez<br>
4) hit assist key to continue attacking the mob that I am facing)<br>
5) begin my 3 song twist after i get the successful mez message<br>
<br>
After it's been locked down, I sing my normal 3 song lineup, and as soon as the 3rd song is done, I:<br>
<br>
1) Stop song<br>
2) Target the add (which is still mezzed)<br>
3) Begin singing mez<br>
4) Re-assist and do the rounds on normal 3 song lineup again<br>
<br>
Doing this I can keep a mob mezzed while missing only a second (at most) of melee time on the mob the MA is attacking.  This works for me since I rely on epic proc for group haste when a better form does not exist.   Considering it only takes a split second to target the add mob, begin singing mez and re-assisting, it's very very easy to do.<br>
<br>
I've seen some bards sit around and just sing mez full time without attacking until they're all dead, but that's really not the thing for me (too inefficient).  If you have an assist key, there's no reason you can't attack while you are waiting for the song to refresh.<br>
<br>
